&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About GlossGenius&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;GlossGenius is the AI-powered system behind the world’s most meaningful appointments, helping 100,000+ service businesses earn more revenue and free up time for the work they love. Our agentic workforce gets more clients in the door, grows profit per appointment, and keeps clients coming back — doing the jobs owners never had time for and couldn’t justify hiring to fill. Businesses on GlossGenius process billions in annual payment volume, and see 65% more revenue using GlossGenius Payments by growing ticket size, rebooking clients at checkout, and saving on processing fees.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Brand at GlossGenius is undertaking a challenging task: creating a visual identity that seamlessly fits both high-growth software environments and appointment-based service businesses, making both feel natural and integrated. As an Associate Creative Director, you&#39;ll own creative execution across brand marketing, web, performance, art direction, and video, while playing a direct role in shaping where the brand goes next. This isn&#39;t a role where you inherit a finished system; you&#39;ll be the one building and evolving it. The pace is real, the bar is high, and the decisions you make will show up everywhere our customers and prospects encounter us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will report to the Creative Director. You must be commutable to our NYC headquarters and will operate in a hybrid environment. We default to being in-office 3–4 days per week with required attendance on Tuesdays and Thursdays.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own creative execution across brand marketing, web, performance, event design, art direction of photography and illustration, and video, from concept through delivery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and evolve brand and visual identity systems that are scalable, consistent, and strong enough to work across every channel we operate in&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage AI-powered design tools to build creative workflows that weren&#39;t previously possible, not just to move faster, but to push output quality to a level that resets the bar&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate business objectives and campaign briefs into high-quality visual assets for digital and physical touchpoints, without losing the brand point of view in the handoff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Direct motion and video with a sharp editorial eye, ensuring moving-image work holds the same craft standard as static brand work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Brand Marketing, Performance, Product, and Events teams to deliver creative that&#39;s cohesive across every touchpoint a customer encounters&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Raise the quality bar consistently, maintaining pixel-perfect attention to detail while operating at the pace the business requires&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We&#39;re Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years of experience in branding and visual design, with a portfolio that demonstrates ownership of brand systems across in-house and/or agency environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You use AI tools to explore concepts faster, pressure-test visual directions, and push output quality, and you have a clear point of view on where AI augments craft and where it doesn&#39;t&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Default to making creative decisions and moving: prefer showing tangible work to stakeholders and iterating over prolonged concepting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expert-level command of Figma, and current on modern design tooling, trends, and best practices across digital and physical channels&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep understanding of design systems and how to apply them consistently at scale across brand, web, performance, and events&lt;/li&gt;
