&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About GlossGenius&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;GlossGenius is the AI-powered system behind the world’s most meaningful appointments, helping 100,000+ service businesses earn more revenue and free up time for the work they love. Our agentic workforce gets more clients in the door, grows profit per appointment, and keeps clients coming back — doing the jobs owners never had time for and couldn’t justify hiring to fill. Businesses on GlossGenius process billions in annual payment volume, and see 65% more revenue using GlossGenius Payments by growing ticket size, rebooking clients at checkout, and saving on processing fees.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;GlossGenius is quickly scaling across its AI-native platform and new business areas, growing in ways that bring meaningful new complexity. Legal is an important part of that foundation, and we need a sharp, pragmatic legal leader who can keep pace with a business that&#39;s moving fast. You&#39;ll be a true enabler of how we scale, partnering directly with leadership to clear the path for the business through thoughtful risk management and judgement. This is a high-ownership, high-visibility, high judgement role with broad scope across commercial, corporate, employment, privacy, and regulatory matters.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will report to the Chief Business Officer&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;This role is based in New York City and operates in an in-person environment. We are in the office for most of the work week.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the full legal function at GlossGenius, covering commercial contracts, corporate governance, employment, data privacy, and regulatory compliance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the primary legal partner to the CEO, CBO, and the entire exec team, proactively advising on strategic initiatives, partnerships, intellectual property, trademark protection and the day-to-day decisions that enable the growth of the business&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Draft, negotiate, and close a wide range of agreements including enterprise contracts, vendor deals, partnership agreements, and financing-related documents&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build the legal infrastructure that scales with us: contract templates, playbooks, approval workflows, and internal policies that give the business speed and confidence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advise on employment and people matters, serving as a trusted resource as the company scales and the complexity of our workforce grows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage outside counsel strategically, with an eye toward keeping spend efficient and outcomes sharp&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shape our approach to the legal and regulatory considerations surrounding AI products and data, as we continue building deeply AI-native capabilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the transformation of legal operations by identifying where AI systems and tools can eliminate low-leverage work, accelerate contract review and drafting, and make the function meaningfully more efficient at scale&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We’re Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;JD from an accredited law school and active bar membership (NY preferred)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years of legal experience, with meaningful time at a top-tier law firm and in-house at a high-growth tech company&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Broad generalist range across commercial, corporate, employment, privacy, and regulatory matters — you&#39;re not a one-practice-area lawyer&lt;/li&gt;
